        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 6:37PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 637 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rochford, or 15 miles north of Hill City, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Silver City, Rochford, Mystic, Roubaix Lake, and Black Fox
Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
west central South Dakota.</instruction>
